-- India's NSE index gains 0.3 pct at pre-open on Fed optimism
-- By Indulal PM
-- Wed Jun 18, 2014 11:46PM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 19 (Reuters) - India's NSE index <.NSEI> rose 0.3 percent in pre-open trading on Thursday on the back of firm global shares after the U.S. Federal Reserve committed to retaining accommodative monetary policy.

The broader NSE index gained 0.29 percent to 7,580.05 points, while the BSE index <.BSESN> was up 0.32 percent at 25,327.09 points.